<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse seaduse &uuml;lesanne </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of Vocational Educational Institutions Act </inglise>
<eesti>Kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse seaduse &uuml;lesanne on s&auml;testada kutse&otilde;ppeasutuse (edaspidi kool) asutamise, &uuml;mberkorraldamise ja tegevuse l&otilde;petamise alused, &otilde;ppekorralduse alused, kooli juhtimise p&otilde;him&otilde;tted, kooli eelarve moodustumise ja finantseerimise alused, kooli liikmeskonna &otilde;igused ja kohustused ning riiklik j&auml;relevalve kooli tegevuse &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>The purpose of the Vocational Educational Institutions Act is to provide the bases for the establishment, reorganisation and closure of vocational educational institutions (hereinafter schools), the bases for organisation of studies, the principles of school management, the bases for school budgeting and financing, the rights and obligations of members of schools, and state supervision over the activities of schools. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli &uuml;lesanne ja liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Function and types of schools </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kooli &uuml;lesanne on luua &otilde;pilastele v&otilde;imalused eluks ja t&ouml;&ouml;ks vajalike teadmiste, oskuste ja eetiliste t&otilde;ekspidamiste omandamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The function of schools is to provide opportunities for students to acquire the knowledge, skills and moral values necessary for life and work. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutse-, eri- ja ametialase koolituse, samuti t&auml;iskasvanute t&ouml;&ouml;alase koolituse korraldamisel arvestab kool &uuml;hiskonna ja t&ouml;&ouml;turu vajadusi. </eesti>
<inglise>Schools shall consider the needs of the society and the labour market upon organising vocational, professional and occupational training, and continuing vocational training. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koolid jagunevad, l&auml;htudes &otilde;pingute alustamiseks n&otilde;utavast haridustasemest, p&otilde;hihariduse baasil tegutsevateks koolideks ja keskhariduse baasil tegutsevateks koolideks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) On the basis of the level of education required for the commencement of studies, schools are divided into schools which operate on the basis of basic education and schools which operate on the basis of secondary education. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel tegutsevad ka koolid, kus on v&otilde;imalik &otilde;ppida nii p&otilde;hi- kui keskhariduse baasil. </eesti>
<inglise>Schools which provide the opportunity to study on the basis of both basic and secondary education also operate pursuant to this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolev seadus reguleerib riigi- ja munitsipaalkoolide tegevust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) This Act regulates the activities of state and municipal schools. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevat seadust kohaldatakse erakoolidele niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd erakooliseadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>This Act applies to private schools in so far as the Private Schools Act does not provide otherwise. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli nimi </eesti>
<inglise>Name of school </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli nimi v&auml;ljendab kooli asukohta ja koolitusala ega tohi olla eksitav haridustaseme suhtes, mida koolis on v&otilde;imalik omandada. </eesti>
<inglise>The name of a school shall express the location and the field of training of the school and shall not be misleading with regard to the level of education which can be acquired at the school. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli &otilde;iguslik seisund </eesti>
<inglise>Legal status of school </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigikool on Haridusministeeriumi hallatav riigiasutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State schools are state agencies administered by the Ministry of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi- v&otilde;i sisekaitseline riigikool on Kaitseministeeriumi v&otilde;i Siseministeeriumi hallatav riigiasutus. </eesti>
<inglise>State schools for national defence and state schools for public defence are state agencies administered by the Ministry of Defence or the Ministry of Internal Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Munitsipaalkool on kohaliku omavalitsuse asutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Municipal schools are local government agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kool tegutseb k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide ning oma p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Schools operate pursuant to this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof and pursuant to their statutes. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riigi- v&otilde;i sisekaitselise riigikooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses v&otilde;ib s&auml;testada k&auml;esolevast seadusest erinevaid s&auml;tteid riigi- v&otilde;i sisekaitselisse riigikooli astumise &uuml;ldtingimuste, &otilde;ppevormide, kooli l&otilde;petamise ning riigi- v&otilde;i sisekaitselise riigikooli struktuuri ja juhtimise osas. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The statutes of a state school for national or public defence may include provisions different from the provisions of this Act concerning the general conditions for the commencement of studies in the state school for national or public defence, the forms of study and graduation from the school or its structure and management. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi ning valla ja linna kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Duty of state, rural municipalities and cities </inglise>
<eesti>Riik ning vald ja linn tagavad soovijatele v&otilde;imaluse p&otilde;hihariduse baasil kutsekeskhariduse omandamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The state, rural municipalities and cities shall ensure the opportunity to acquire secondary vocational education on the basis of basic education for those interested therein. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli asutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of Schools </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Asutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigikooli asutab asjaomase ministri ettepanekul Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Government of the Republic shall establish a state school on the proposal of the appropriate minister. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigikooli asutamise ettepaneku teeb Haridusministeerium. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Ministry of Education shall make proposals for the establishment of state schools. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui riigikooli asutamise ettepaneku teeb Siseministeerium v&otilde;i Kaitseministeerium, koosk&otilde;lastatakse ettepanek Haridusministeeriumiga. </eesti>
<inglise>If the Ministry of Internal Affairs or the Ministry of Defence makes a proposal for the establishment of a state school, the Ministry of Education shall grant consent to the proposal. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Haridusministeerium n&otilde;ustub riigikooli asutamise ettepanekuga, kui on t&auml;idetud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatud kooli asutamise kohustuslikud tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Ministry of Education shall grant consent to a proposal for the establishment of a state school if the mandatory requirements for the establishment of a school provided for in subsection (4) of this section are fulfilled. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kooli asutamise kohustuslikud tingimused on j&auml;rgmised: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The mandatory requirements for the establishment of a school are the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kutse-, eri- ja ametiala vastava riikliku &otilde;ppekava n&otilde;uetele vastava &otilde;ppekava olemasolu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) existence of a curriculum or curricula which conform to the requirements of the national curricula for the corresponding vocations, professions and occupations; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;uetele vastavate pedagoogide olemasolu; </eesti>
<inglise>2) existence of teachers who meet the qualification requirements provided for in legislation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kooli tegevuseks vajalike &otilde;pperuumide (hoonete) ja sisustuse olemasolu, mis vastab p&otilde;hikoolile ja g&uuml;mnaasiumile kehtestatud tervisekaitse n&otilde;uetele, ja &otilde;ppekavast tulenevalt &otilde;ppepraktika ruumide olemasolu, mis vastab t&ouml;&ouml;ruumidele kehtestatud tervisekaitse normidele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) existence of study rooms (buildings) and furnishings which conform to the health protection requirements established for basic schools and upper secondary schools, and the existence of facilities for practical training based on the curriculum which conform to the health protection standards established for workrooms; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse olemasolu. </eesti>
<inglise>4) existence of the statutes of the school. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Riigikool asutatakse Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) State schools shall be established pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Munitsipaalkooli asutab kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu otsusel valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus Haridusministeeriumi v&auml;ljaantud koolitusloa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Municipal schools shall be established by a rural municipality government or city government by a resolution of the local government council on the basis of an education licence issued by the Ministry of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rus </eesti>
<inglise>Statutes of schools </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rus peab sisaldama j&auml;rgmisi andmeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The statutes of a school shall contain the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kooli t&auml;ielik nimi, liik ja asukoht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the full name, type and location of the school; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ministeeriumi nimi, kelle valitsemisalasse kool kuulub, v&otilde;i vastava valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse nimi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name of the ministry in whose area of government the school is located, or the name of the corresponding rural municipality government or city government; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kooli tegevuse eesm&auml;rk ja &uuml;lesanded; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the purpose of the activities and functions of the school; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kooli struktuur ja struktuuri&uuml;ksuste &uuml;lesanded; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the structure of the school and the functions of its structural units; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &otilde;ppekeel; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the language of instruction; </inglise>
<eesti>6) &otilde;ppekorralduse alused; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the bases for organisation of studies; </inglise>
<eesti>7) &otilde;pilaste, pedagoogide ja teiste t&ouml;&ouml;tajate &otilde;igused ning kohustused; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the rights and obligations of students, teachers and other employees; </inglise>
<eesti>8) finantseerimise, majandamise ja asjaajamise alused. </eesti>
<inglise>8) the bases for financing, management and administration. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigikooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse kinnitab minister, kelle juhitava ministeeriumi valitsemisalasse riigikool kuulub. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The statutes of a state school shall be approved by the minister who directs the ministry in whose area of government the school is located. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Munitsipaalkooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse kinnitab valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The rural municipality council or the city council shall approve the statutes of a municipal school. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolitusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Education licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koolitusluba on riiklik dokument, mis annab munitsipaalkoolile &otilde;iguse viia l&auml;bi &otilde;pet koolitusloal m&auml;rgitud vastava kutse-, eri- ja ametiala &otilde;ppekava alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An education licence is a public document which grants a municipal school the right to provide instruction on the basis of curricula for the corresponding vocations, professions and occupations indicated on the education licence. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolituslubade v&auml;ljaandmise ja t&uuml;histamise korra ning koolitusloa vormi kehtestab haridusminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for the issue and revocation of education licences and the format of education licences shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koolitusluba on t&auml;htajaline. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Education licences are issued for a specified term. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolitusluba antakse &otilde;ppekavaga m&auml;&auml;ratud nominaalse &otilde;ppeaja kestuse ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>Education licences are issued for the duration of the standard period of study determined in the curriculum. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Koolitusloa saamiseks esitab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus taotluse Haridusministeeriumile hiljemalt neli kuud enne &otilde;ppeaasta algust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to obtain an education licence, a rural municipality government or city government shall submit an application to the Ministry of Education not later than four months before the beginning of an academic year. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotlusele lisatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatud andmed kooli asutamise kohustuslike tingimuste t&auml;itmise kohta ja maavanema ning omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liidu kirjalikud arvamused munitsipaalkooli asutamise vajalikkuse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Information concerning the fulfilment of the mandatory requirements for the establishment of a school provided for in subsection 5 (4) of this Act and the written opinions of the county governor and the local government association concerning the need to establish a municipal school shall be annexed to the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Haridusministeerium vaatab koolitusloa taotluse l&auml;bi &uuml;he kuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Ministry of Education shall review the application for an education licence within one month. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Haridusministeerium teavitab koolitusloa taotlejat koolitusloa v&auml;ljaandmisest kirjalikult k&uuml;mne t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast vastava otsuse tegemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Ministry of Education shall notify the applicant for an education licence of the issue of an education licence in writing within ten working days after the corresponding decision is made. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Koolitusloa v&auml;ljastamise eest tuleb tasuda riigil&otilde;ivu. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A state fee shall be paid for the issue of an education licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Haridusministeerium ei anna koolitusluba, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The Ministry of Education shall not issue an education licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatud andmed kooli asutamise kohustuslike tingimuste t&auml;itmise kohta puuduvad v&otilde;i ei vasta &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) no information concerning the fulfilment of the mandatory requirements for the establishment of a school provided for in subsection 5 (4) of this Act is given or the information does not conform to the requirements established by legislation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) puuduvad maavanema ja omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liidu kirjalikud arvamused munitsipaalkooli asutamise vajalikkuse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) written opinions of the county governor and the local government association concerning the need to found a municipal school are not provided; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riigil&otilde;iv on tasumata; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the state fee is not paid; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &otilde;ppekavale m&auml;&auml;ratud ekspertiisi tulemused on negatiivsed. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the results of an assessment conducted with regard to the curriculum are negative. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Haridusministeerium teatab keeldumise p&otilde;hjustest koolitusloa taotlejale kirjalikult k&uuml;mne t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast vastava otsuse tegemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The Ministry of Education shall notify the applicant for an education licence of the reasons for refusal in writing within ten working days after the corresponding decision is made. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppekava ekspertiis </eesti>
<inglise>Assessment of curriculum </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Haridusminister v&otilde;ib anda k&auml;skkirja &otilde;ppekavale ekspertiisi tegemiseks, moodustades selleks ajutise komisjoni &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Education may issue a directive to conduct an assessment of a curriculum and form an ad hoc committee for that purpose pursuant to the procedure provided by legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;ppekavale tehtavast ekspertiisist teatatakse koolitusloa taotlejale viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast vastava k&auml;skkirja andmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The applicant for an education licence shall be notified of the assessment of a curriculum within five working days after the issue of the corresponding directive. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ekspertiisikulude kandmise otsustab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud komisjon. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The committee specified in subsection (1) of this section shall decide who bears the costs of an assessment. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud koolitusloa taotluse l&auml;bivaatamise t&auml;htaeg pikeneb &otilde;ppekavale ekspertiisi tegemise aja v&otilde;rra, kuid mitte rohkem kui kahe kuu v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The term for reviewing an application for an education licence specified in subsection 7 (4) of this Act shall be extended by the period of conducting an assessment of the curriculum but for not more than two months. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolitusloa t&uuml;histamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of education licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Haridusministeeriumil on &otilde;igus t&uuml;histada koolitusluba, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Ministry of Education has the right to revoke an education licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) riikliku j&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus ilmneb, et kooli tegevus on vastuolus seadusega v&otilde;i selle alusel v&auml;ljaantud &otilde;igusaktidega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in the course of state supervision it becomes evident that the activities of the school are in conflict with law or legislation issued on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kool ei ole etten&auml;htud t&auml;htajaks t&auml;itnud kooli &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatustegevuse &uuml;le riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet teostava organi poolt temale tehtud ettekirjutust; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the school has not, during the prescribed term, complied with a precept issued thereto by a body exercising state supervision over the educational activities of the school; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kool ei ole &uuml;he aasta jooksul p&auml;rast koolitusloa v&auml;ljaandmist alustanud &otilde;ppetegevust v&otilde;i on &otilde;ppetegevuse peatanud v&otilde;i l&otilde;petanud. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the school has not commenced the provision of education within one year after the issue of an education licence or has suspended or terminated the provision of education. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Haridusministeerium teatab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele munitsipaalkoolile v&auml;ljaantud koolitusloa t&uuml;histamisest kirjalikult viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast vastava otsuse tegemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Ministry of Education shall notify a rural municipality government or city government of the revocation of an education licence issued to a municipal school in writing within five working days after the corresponding decision is made. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppekorraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of Studies </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppekavad </eesti>
<inglise>Curricula </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koolis toimub &otilde;pe kutse-, eri- ja ametiala riikliku &otilde;ppekava alusel koostatud &otilde;ppekava j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Instruction in schools shall be carried out according to curricula prepared on the basis of the national curricula for vocations, professions and occupations. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolis v&otilde;ib toimuda &otilde;pe kutse-, eri- ja ametiala riikliku &otilde;ppekava alusel koostatud kutsealase eelkoolituse &otilde;ppekava j&auml;rgi, mis v&otilde;imaldab p&otilde;hiharidust v&otilde;i &uuml;ldkeskharidust omandavatel &otilde;pilastel omandada p&otilde;hi- ja &uuml;ldkeskhariduse riikliku &otilde;ppekavaga etten&auml;htud valikainete raames esmased kutse-, eri- v&otilde;i ametialased teadmised ja oskused. </eesti>
<inglise>Instruction in schools may be carried out according to the national curricula for preliminary vocational training prepared on the basis of the national curricula for vocations, professions and occupations which allows students acquiring basic education or general secondary education to acquire primary vocational, professional and occupational knowledge and skills within the framework of elective subjects prescribed by the national curriculum of basic education and general secondary education. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Keskhariduse baasil tegutsevates koolides v&otilde;ib &otilde;pe toimuda ka k&otilde;rgharidusstandardile vastava kutsek&otilde;rghariduse &otilde;ppekava j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Instruction in schools which operate on the basis of secondary education may also be carried out according to a curriculum of higher vocational education which conforms to the Standard of Higher Education. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsek&otilde;rghariduse &otilde;ppekava rakendamisele koolis laienevad rakendusk&otilde;rgkooli seaduses (RT I 1998, 61, 980; 1999, 10, 150; 102, 908; 2000, 54, 350; 78, 496; 2001, 65, 375) kehtestatud n&otilde;uded. </eesti>
<inglise>The requirements established by the Institutions of Applied Higher Education Act (RT I 1998, 61, 980; 1999, 10, 150; 102, 908; 2000, 54, 350; 78, 496; 2001, 65, 375) apply to the implementation of curricula of higher vocational education in schools. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutse-, eri- ja ametialade riiklikud &otilde;ppekavad </eesti>
<inglise>National curricula for vocations, professions and occupations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kutse-, eri- ja ametialade riiklikud &otilde;ppekavad m&auml;&auml;ravad kindlaks kutse-, eri- ja ametialase koolituse &uuml;lesanded, &uuml;ld- ja tasemen&otilde;uded &otilde;pingute alustamiseks ning kooli l&otilde;petamiseks, kohustuslike &otilde;ppeainete loetelu ja &otilde;pingute kogumahu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The national curricula for vocations, professions and occupations shall determine the functions of vocational, professional and occupational training, the general and level requirements for the commencement of studies and graduation from schools, the list of compulsory subjects and the total extent of studies. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kutse-, eri- ja ametialade riiklike &otilde;ppekavade koostamisel l&auml;htutakse kutsen&otilde;ukogu poolt kinnitatud kutsestandarditest ning kutse-, eri- ja ametialade riiklikele &otilde;ppekavadele kehtestatud &uuml;ldn&otilde;uetest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The national curricula for vocations, professions and occupations shall be prepared on the basis of the professional standards approved by a professional council and the general requirements established for the national curricula for vocations, professions and occupations. </inglise>
<eesti>(19.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.19.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 3, 7) </eesti>
<inglise>(19.12.2000 entered into force 19.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 3, 7) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kutse-, eri- ja ametialade riiklike &otilde;ppekavade &uuml;ldn&otilde;uded kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Government of the Republic shall approve the general requirements for the national curricula for vocations, professions and occupations. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutse-, eri- ja ametialade riiklikud &otilde;ppekavad koostab Haridusministeerium, v&otilde;ttes aluseks kutsen&otilde;ukogu poolt kinnitatud kutsestandardid. </eesti>
<inglise>The Ministry of Education shall prepare the national curricula for vocations, professions and occupations on the basis of the professional standards approved by a professional council. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklikud &otilde;ppekavad valdkonniti kinnitab haridusminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Education shall, by a regulation, approve the national curricula by speciality. </inglise>
<eesti>(19.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.19.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 3, 7) </eesti>
<inglise>(19.12.2000 entered into force 19.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 3, 7) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. (Kehtetu - 19.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.19.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 3, 7) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. (Repealed - 19.12.2000 entered into force 19.01.2001 - RT I 2001, 3, 7) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli &otilde;ppekava </eesti>
<inglise>School curriculum </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kooli &otilde;ppekava on vastava kutse-, eri- ja ametialaga seotud &otilde;pingute alusdokument, mis m&auml;&auml;rab &otilde;ppeainete loetelu koos mahu ja sisu &uuml;ldiseloomustusega, &otilde;ppeainete valiku v&otilde;imalused ja tingimused ning n&otilde;uded &otilde;pingute alustamiseks ja kooli l&otilde;petamiseks, sealhulgas l&otilde;put&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A school curriculum is the source document for studies related to the corresponding vocations, professions and occupations which sets out the list of subjects together with the extent and general outline of the subjects, the possibilities of and conditions for choosing subjects and the requirements for the commencement of studies and graduation from the school, including the requirements for the preparation of final papers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kool koostab &otilde;ppekava iga kutse-, eri- ja ametiala jaoks, mida koolis on v&otilde;imalik omandada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A school shall prepare a curriculum for every vocation, profession and occupation which can be acquired in the school. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kooli &otilde;ppekava ja selles tehtavad muudatused ning t&auml;iendused kinnitab kooli direktor. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The head of a school shall approve the school curriculum and amendments thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kooli &otilde;ppekava ja selles tehtavad muudatused ning t&auml;iendused registreeritakse Haridusministeeriumis vastavalt haridusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud korrale. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A school curriculum and amendments thereto shall be registered in the Ministry of Education pursuant to the procedure established by a regulation of the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli astumise tingimused ja kord </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions and procedure for commencement of studies in school </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kooli, mis tegutseb p&otilde;hihariduse baasil, v&otilde;ivad &otilde;ppima asuda isikud, kellel on p&otilde;hiharidus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Persons who have completed basic education may commence studies in a school which operates on the basis of basic education. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli, mis tegutseb keskhariduse baasil, v&otilde;ivad &otilde;ppima asuda isikud, kellel on &uuml;ld- v&otilde;i kutsekeskharidus. </eesti>
<inglise>Persons who have completed general secondary education or secondary vocational education may commence studies in a school which operates on the basis of secondary education. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;pilaste vastuv&otilde;tu korra kinnitab haridusminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for admission of students shall be approved by a regulation of the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;pilasel on &otilde;igus &uuml;hes koolis alustatud &otilde;pinguid j&auml;tkata vabade kohtade olemasolul teises koolis samal kutse-, eri- ja ametialal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If vacant places exist, students have the right to continue their studies commenced in one school in the same vocation, profession or occupation in another school. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;leminekul teisele kutse-, eri- ja ametialale peab &otilde;pilane sooritama k&otilde;ik selles &otilde;ppekavas etten&auml;htud eksamid ja arvestused, mida eelmise kooli &otilde;ppekava ei sisaldanud. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon transfer to another vocation, profession or occupation, a student shall pass all the examinations and assessments prescribed in the curriculum for the vocation, profession or occupation which were not included in the curriculum of the previous school. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&otilde;hihariduse baasil tegutseva kooli pooleli j&auml;tnud &otilde;pilasel on keskhariduse omandamiseks &otilde;igus j&auml;tkata &otilde;pinguid g&uuml;mnaasiumis haridusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud tingimusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Students who have interrupted their studies in a school which operates on the basis of basic education have the right to continue studies in an upper secondary school in order to acquire secondary education under the conditions established by a regulation of the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Puudega inimestele tagatakse koolis &otilde;ppimise v&otilde;imalused Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Opportunities for disabled persons to study in schools shall be ensured under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) (Kehtetu - 13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(5) (Repealed - 13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kooli vastuv&otilde;etud &otilde;pilasele v&auml;ljastatakse &otilde;pilaspilet. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Student cards shall be issued to students admitted to a school. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;pilaspileti vormi ja v&auml;ljaandmise korra kehtestab haridusminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The format of and procedure for the issue of student cards shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsealane eelkoolitus </eesti>
<inglise>Preliminary vocational training </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kool v&otilde;imaldab p&otilde;hi- ja &uuml;ldkeskhariduse riikliku &otilde;ppekavaga etten&auml;htud valikainete raames ja kutsealase eelkoolituse &otilde;ppekava j&auml;rgi kutsealast eelkoolitust p&otilde;hiharidust v&otilde;i &uuml;ldkeskharidust omandavatele &otilde;pilastele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A school shall ensure preliminary vocational training for students acquiring basic education or general secondary education within the framework of elective subjects prescribed by the national curriculum of basic education and general secondary education and according to the national curricula for preliminary vocational training. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsealase eelkoolituse l&auml;bimise kohta v&auml;ljastab kool &otilde;pilasele t&otilde;endi, mille alusel tehakse kanne &otilde;pilase p&otilde;hikooli v&otilde;i g&uuml;mnaasiumi l&otilde;putunnistusele. </eesti>
<inglise>The school shall issue certificates concerning completion of preliminary vocational training to students and on the basis of the certificates entries shall be made on the students' graduation certificates from basic schools or upper secondary schools. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kool v&otilde;imaldab kutsealase eelkoolituse &otilde;ppekava j&auml;rgi kutsealast eelkoolitust ka nendele p&otilde;hiharidust omandavatele &otilde;pilastele, kes on v&auml;ljunud koolikohustuse east ja omandavad p&otilde;hiharidust &otilde;htuses v&otilde;i kaug&otilde;ppe vormis p&otilde;hikooli- ja g&uuml;mnaasiumiseadusega (RT I 1993, 63, 892; 1999, 42, 497; 79, 730; 2000, 33, 195; 54, 349; 95, 611; 2001, 50, 288; 75, 454) s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A school shall ensure preliminary vocational training according to the national curricula for preliminary vocational training also for those students acquiring basic education who are beyond the minimum school-leaving age and acquire basic education in the form of evening courses or distance learning on the bases and pursuant to the procedure provided by the Basic Schools and Upper Secondary Schools Act (RT I 1993, 63, 892; 1999, 42, 497; 79, 730; 2000, 33, 195; 54, 349; 95, 611; 2001, 50, 288; 75, 454). </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsealase eelkoolituse l&auml;bimise kohta v&auml;ljastab kool &otilde;pilasele t&otilde;endi. </eesti>
<inglise>The school shall issue certificates concerning completion of preliminary vocational training to students. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud kutsealase eelkoolituse korraldamiseks s&otilde;lmitakse leping kooli ja selle p&otilde;hikooli v&otilde;i g&uuml;mnaasiumi vahel, kus &otilde;pilane omandab p&otilde;hi- v&otilde;i &uuml;ldkeskharidust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to organise preliminary vocational training specified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section, a contract shall be entered into between a school and the basic school or upper secondary school where a student acquires basic education or general secondary education. </inglise>
<eesti>Leping koosk&otilde;lastatakse kooli asukohaj&auml;rgse maavanemaga ning selle kohustuslikud tingimused on: </eesti>
<inglise>The contract shall be approved by the county governor of the location of the school and the mandatory terms and conditions for the contract shall be: </inglise>
<eesti>1) andmed koolide kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) information on the schools; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kutsealase eelkoolituse maht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the scope of preliminary vocational training; </inglise>
<eesti>3) koolituskohtade arv; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the number of student places; </inglise>
<eesti>4) koolituskoha maksumus; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the cost of a student place; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kutsealase eelkoolituse eest tasumise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the procedure for payment for preliminary vocational training; </inglise>
<eesti>6) poolte &otilde;igused ja kohustused; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the rights and obligations of the parties; </inglise>
<eesti>7) poolte vastutus. </eesti>
<inglise>7) the liability of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kooli juurde, kus toimub kutsekeskhariduse omandamine muusika v&otilde;i koreograafia valdkonna &otilde;ppekavade j&auml;rgi, v&otilde;ib moodustada vastava kutsealase eelkoolituse korraldamiseks &otilde;ppegruppe neljanda kuni &uuml;heksanda klassi &otilde;pilastele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) At schools where secondary vocational education is acquired according to curricula in the field of music or choreography, training groups for students from year four to year nine may be formed in order to organise the corresponding preliminary vocational training. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsealase eelkoolituse l&auml;bimise kohta v&auml;ljastab kool &otilde;pilasele t&otilde;endi. </eesti>
<inglise>The schools shall issue certificates concerning completion of preliminary vocational training to students. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hihariduse omandamine toimub p&otilde;hikooli- ja g&uuml;mnaasiumiseadusega s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The acquisition of basic education shall be organised on the basis of and pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Basic Schools and Upper Secondary Schools Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kutsealase eelkoolituse l&auml;binud &otilde;pilane on omandanud kooli &otilde;ppekavas etten&auml;htud esmased kutse-, eri- v&otilde;i ametialased teadmised ja oskused ning v&otilde;ib j&auml;tkata &otilde;pinguid koolis k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras, kusjuures kooli &otilde;ppekava t&auml;itmisel arvestatakse eelkoolituse &otilde;ppekava l&auml;bimisel omandatud teadmisi ja oskusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A student who has completed preliminary vocational training has acquired the primary vocational, professional and occupational knowledge and skills prescribed by the school curriculum and may continue studies in the school under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by this Act, and upon completion of the school curriculum, the knowledge and skills acquired during completion of the curricula for preliminary training shall be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsekeskharidus </eesti>
<inglise>Secondary vocational education </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koolis omandatakse kutsekeskharidus kutse-, eri- ja ametiala riiklikule &otilde;ppekavale vastava kutsekeskhariduse &otilde;ppekava alusel, kusjuures &otilde;ppekava nominaalkestus p&otilde;hihariduse baasil &otilde;ppivatele &otilde;pilastele on v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat ja keskhariduse baasil v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks aasta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Secondary vocational education is acquired in a school on the basis of a curriculum of secondary vocational education which conforms to the national curricula for vocations, professions and occupations; the standard period of study for students who study on the basis of basic education is at least three years and, for students who study on the basis of secondary education, at least one year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&otilde;hihariduse baasil &otilde;ppivad &otilde;pilased omandavad &uuml;ldhariduslikke &otilde;ppeaineid v&auml;hemalt 50 &otilde;ppen&auml;dala ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Students who study on the basis of basic education shall complete at least fifty weeks of study of general educational subjects. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsek&otilde;rgharidus </eesti>
<inglise>Higher vocational education </inglise>
<eesti>Koolis omandatakse k&otilde;rgharidus kutsek&otilde;rghariduse &otilde;ppekava alusel, mille &otilde;ppekavaga m&auml;&auml;ratud &otilde;ppeaja nominaalkestus on kolm kuni neli aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>Higher education is acquired in a school on the basis of a curriculum of higher vocational education, and the duration of the standard period of study of higher education is three to four years as determined by the curriculum. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.01.99 j&otilde;ust.15.02.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 150) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.01.99 entered into force 15.02.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 150) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppepraktika </eesti>
<inglise>Practical training </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kooli, &otilde;pilase v&otilde;i tema seadusliku esindaja ja riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse asutuse, avalik-&otilde;igusliku v&otilde;i era&otilde;igusliku juriidilise isiku v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja vahelised suhted &otilde;pilaste &otilde;ppepraktika korraldamisel reguleeritakse nende vahel s&otilde;lmitava lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon organisation of the practical training of students, the relations between a school, a student or his or her legal representative and a state agency or local government agency, a legal person in public law, legal person in private law or a sole proprietor shall be regulated by a contract entered into by them. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud leping s&otilde;lmitakse v&auml;hemalt 10 p&auml;eva enne &otilde;ppepraktika algust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) A contract specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be entered into at least ten days before the practical training begins. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (2)) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud lepingu kohustuslikud tingimused on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (2)) The mandatory terms and conditions for a contract specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &otilde;ppepraktika alustamise ja l&otilde;petamise aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the time of commencement and completion of the practical training; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;ppepraktika kestus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the duration of the practical training; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &otilde;ppepraktika toimumise koht ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the place and address where the practical training is conducted; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &otilde;ppepraktika &uuml;lesande kirjeldus l&auml;htuvalt kooli &otilde;ppekavast; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the description of the function of the practical training on the basis of the school curriculum; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &otilde;ppepraktikal viibiva &otilde;pilase &otilde;igused ja kohustused; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the rights and obligations of students during the practical training; </inglise>
<eesti>6) &otilde;ppepraktika korraldaja &otilde;igused ja kohustused; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the rights and obligations of the organiser of the practical training; </inglise>
<eesti>7) kooli &otilde;igused ja kohustused; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the rights and obligations of the school; </inglise>
<eesti>8) andmed &otilde;ppepraktika korraldaja ning koolipoolse &otilde;ppepraktika juhendaja kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>8) information on the organiser of the practical training and the practical training instructor of the school; </inglise>
<eesti>9) lepingu muutmise ja l&otilde;petamise alused ja kord; </eesti>
<inglise>9) the bases and procedure for amendment and termination of the contract; </inglise>
<eesti>10) vaidluste lahendamise kord. </eesti>
<inglise>10) the procedure for the resolution of disputes. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;ppepraktika l&auml;biviimiseks loodud ametikohad, sealhulgas kooli &otilde;ppet&ouml;&ouml;kojas ja &otilde;ppemajandis, peavad vastama tingimustele, mis v&otilde;imaldavad &otilde;ppekavaga kehtestatud n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Positions created for conducting practical training, including positions in the school workshop and the school farm, shall allow compliance with the requirements established by the curriculum. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;ppepraktikal viibimise ajal laienevad &otilde;pilastele t&ouml;&ouml;kaitsealased &otilde;igusaktid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Legislation related to occupational health and safety applies to students during practical training. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppekeel </eesti>
<inglise>Language of instruction </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppekeel on koolis eesti keel. </eesti>
<inglise>The language of instruction in schools is Estonian. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppekeelena teiste keelte kasutamise otsustab haridusminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Education shall decide on the use of other languages as languages of instruction. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppevormid </eesti>
<inglise>Forms of study </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;pe toimub p&auml;eva-, &otilde;htu- ja kaug&otilde;ppe vormis. </eesti>
<inglise>Instruction is provided in the form of daytime study, evening courses or distance learning. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppeaasta </eesti>
<inglise>Academic year </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;ppeaasta koosneb &otilde;ppeajast, praktikaajast, eksamiperioodist ja &otilde;ppevaheajast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Class time, the period of practical training, the examination session and school holidays form an academic year. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;ppeaeg koos eksamiperioodi ja praktikaajaga on v&auml;hemalt 40 &otilde;ppen&auml;dalat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Class time together with the examination session and period of practical training shall amount to at least forty weeks of study. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppevaheaja kogukestus on v&auml;hemalt kaheksa n&auml;dalat aastas. </eesti>
<inglise>The total duration of school holidays shall be at least eight weeks in a year. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Hindamine </eesti>
<inglise>Assessment </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;pilaste teadmisi, oskusi ja vilumusi kutsekeskhariduse omandamisel hinnatakse p&otilde;hikooli- ja g&uuml;mnaasiumiseaduses (RT I 1993, 63, 892; 1999, 42, 497; 79, 730; 2000, 33, 195; 54, 349; 95, 611; 2001, 50, 288; 75, 454) s&auml;testatud skaala alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>The knowledge, skills and experience of students upon acquiring secondary vocational education shall be assessed pursuant to the scale provided for in the Basic Schools and Upper Secondary Schools Act (RT I 1993, 63, 892; 1999, 42, 497; 79, 730; 2000, 33, 195; 54, 349; 95, 611; 2001, 50, 288; 75, 454). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Graduation from school </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kool loetakse l&otilde;petatuks p&auml;rast vastava &otilde;ppekava t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person is deemed to have graduated from a school after completion of the corresponding curriculum. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) P&otilde;hihariduse baasil kutsekeskharidust omandavate muu &otilde;ppekeelega &otilde;ppegruppide l&otilde;petajad sooritavad kooli l&otilde;petamiseks ka eesti keele riigieksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) In order to graduate from a school, the graduates of training groups with other languages of instruction who acquire secondary vocational education on the basis of basic education shall pass a state examination in the Estonian language. </inglise>
<eesti>Eesti keele riigieksami sooritamine toimub keeleseaduse (RT I 1995, 23, 334; 1996, 37, 739; 40, 773; 1997, 69, 1110; 1998, 98/99, 1618; 1999, 1, 1; 16, 275; 60, 618; 2000, 51, 326; 2001, 58, 354; 65, 375) ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>A state examination in the Estonian language shall be passed under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by the Language Act (RT I 1995, 23, 334; 1996, 37, 739; 40, 773; 1997, 69, 1110; 1998, 98/99, 1618; 1999, 1, 1; 16, 275; 60, 618; 2000, 51, 326; 2001, 58, 354; 65, 375) and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kooli l&otilde;petamist t&otilde;endab kooli l&otilde;putunnistus, kutsek&otilde;rghariduse &otilde;ppekava l&auml;bimisel diplom, mille vormi ja v&auml;ljaandmise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The graduation from a school shall be certified by a graduation certificate, and, upon completion of a curriculum of higher vocational education, by a diploma, the format and procedure for issue of which is established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.01.99 j&otilde;ust.15.02.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 150) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.01.99 entered into force 15.02.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 150) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kooli v&auml;ljaantud l&otilde;putunnistused kantakse Haridusministeeriumi l&otilde;pudokumentide registrisse haridusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Graduation certificates issued by schools shall be entered in the register of graduation documents pursuant to the procedure established by a regulation of the Ministry of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iskasvanute t&ouml;&ouml;alane koolitus </eesti>
<inglise>Continuing vocational training </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kool korraldab t&auml;iskasvanute t&ouml;&ouml;alast koolitust haridusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A school shall organise continuing vocational training under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by a regulation of the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) (Kehtetu - 13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli juhtimine ja struktuur </eesti>
<inglise>Management and Structure of Schools </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Direktor </eesti>
<inglise>Head of school </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kooli juhib direktor, kelle &uuml;lesanne on tagada kooli tulemuslik t&ouml;&ouml;. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A school shall be managed by the head of the school whose function is to ensure the effective operation of the school. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Direktor kannab oma p&auml;devuse piires vastutust kooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruselise tegevuse, &uuml;ldseisundi ja arengu ning rahaliste vahendite &otilde;igusp&auml;rase kasutamise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The head of a school shall bear liability within the limits of his or her competence for the activities of the school according to the statutes and for the general state and development of the school and the legitimate use of financial resources of the school. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Direktor annab oma tegevusest aru kooli n&otilde;ukogule ja teda ametisse kinnitanule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The head of a school shall report to the school board and to the person who authorised him or her to office. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Direktor: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The head of a school shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) esindab kooli ja tegutseb kooli nimel, teostab tehinguid, mis on suunatud tema seaduses s&auml;testatud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) represent the school and act in the name of the school and conclude transactions directed at the performance of his or her duties provided by law; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juhatab kooli &otilde;ppen&otilde;ukogu; </eesti>
<inglise>2) chair the teachers' council; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tagab kooli n&otilde;ukogu ja &otilde;ppen&otilde;ukogu otsuste t&auml;itmise; </eesti>
<inglise>3) ensure the implementation of decisions of the school board and teachers' council; </inglise>
<eesti>4) m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks direktori asendamise korra; </eesti>
<inglise>4) determine the procedure for the substitution of the head of the school; </inglise>
<eesti>5) on t&ouml;&ouml;andjaks personalile ja kinnitab k&auml;skkirjaga nende ametijuhendid; </eesti>
<inglise>5) act as an employer of the staff and approve their job descriptions by a directive; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kinnitab k&auml;skkirjaga kooli sisekorra- ja asjaajamise eeskirjad; </eesti>
<inglise>6) approve the rules of internal procedure and administration of the school by a directive; </inglise>
<eesti>7) tagab kooli eelarveprojekti koostamise ning eelarve t&auml;itmise; </eesti>
<inglise>7) ensure the preparation of a draft school budget and the implementation of the budget; </inglise>
<eesti>8) tagab seadusega etten&auml;htud aruannete koostamise ja esitamise; </eesti>
<inglise>8) ensure the preparation and submission of reports prescribed by law; </inglise>
<eesti>9) lahendab teisi talle antud k&uuml;simusi. </eesti>
<inglise>9) resolve other issues delegated to him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Direktor annab k&auml;skkirju. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The head of a school shall issue directives. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Direktori ametisse kinnitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment of head of school to office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kooli direktori vaba ametikoha t&auml;itmiseks korraldatakse avalik konkurss. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to fill a vacant position of the head of a school, a public competition shall be organised. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkursi viib l&auml;bi kooli n&otilde;ukogu haridusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The school board shall conduct the competition pursuant to the procedure established by a regulation of the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Direktor kinnitatakse konkursitulemuste alusel ametisse konkursil v&auml;ljakuulutatud t&auml;htajaks, kuid mitte kauemaks kui viieks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The head of a school shall be appointed to office on the basis of the competition results for the term declared at the competition but for not more than five years. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigikooli direktoriga s&otilde;lmib, muudab ning l&otilde;petab t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu minister, kelle juhitava ministeeriumi valitsemisalasse kool kuulub, munitsipaalkooli direktoriga s&otilde;lmib, muudab ning l&otilde;petab t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse ettepanekul. </eesti>
<inglise>The employment contract of the head of a state school shall be entered into, amended or terminated by the minister who directs the ministry in whose area of government the state school is located, and the employment contract of the head of a municipal school shall be entered into, amended or terminated by the rural municipality mayor or city mayor on the proposal of the rural municipality government or city government. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppen&otilde;ukogu </eesti>
<inglise>Teachers' council </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koolil on &otilde;ppen&otilde;ukogu, kelle &uuml;lesandeks on kooli &otilde;ppetegevusega seotud k&uuml;simuste lahendamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A school has a teachers' council whose function is to resolve issues related to schooling. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;ppen&otilde;ukogu liikmeteks on kooli pedagoogid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The teachers of a school shall be the members of a teachers' council. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;ppen&otilde;ukogu t&ouml;&ouml;kord s&auml;testatakse kooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The rules of procedure of a teachers' council shall be provided for in the statutes of the school. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli n&otilde;ukogu </eesti>
<inglise>School board </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kooli n&otilde;ukogu suunab kooli tegevust ja otsustab kooli arengu, vara ja eelarvega seotud k&uuml;simusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A school board shall direct the activities of a school and resolve issues related to the development, assets and budget of the school. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli n&otilde;ukogu on viie- kuni &uuml;heksaliikmeline ja selle moodustab riigikooli puhul minister, kelle valitsemisalasse kool kuulub, munitsipaalkooli puhul aga vastav valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>A school board shall consist of five to nine members and shall be formed, in the case of state schools, by the minister in whose area of government the school is located and, in the case of municipal schools, by the corresponding rural municipality or city government. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kooli n&otilde;ukogu moodustatakse ministeeriumi, kelle valitsemisalasse kool kuulub, vastava valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse v&otilde;i kohalike omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liidu, vastava kutse-, eri- ja ametialaga seotud t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate (teenistujate) registreeritud &uuml;hingute ja kutse&uuml;hingute ning T&ouml;&ouml;turuameti piirkondlike t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;iveametite esindajatest kolmeks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The board of a school shall be formed for a term of three years and shall comprise representatives of the corresponding rural municipality or city government or the local government association, representatives of the registered organisations and trade unions of employers and workers (employees) connected with the corresponding vocations, professions and occupations and representatives of the regional employment offices of the Labour Market Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>(2 (1)) N&otilde;ukogu liikmed v&otilde;ib minister, kelle valitsemisalasse kool kuulub, v&otilde;i vastav valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus tagasi kutsuda juhul, kui n&otilde;ukogu koosseis ei ole kokku tulnud kolme kuu jooksul p&auml;rast n&otilde;ukogu koosseisu kinnitamist v&otilde;i kui n&otilde;ukogu ei ole t&auml;itnud talle k&auml;esoleva seadusega pandud &uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2 (1)) The minister in whose area of government a school is located, or the corresponding rural municipality or city government may remove the members of the board if the members of the board have not convened within three months after approval of the members of the board or if the board does not perform the duties imposed thereon by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kooli n&otilde;ukogu: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A school board shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kinnitab kooli arengukava; </eesti>
<inglise>1) approve the development plan of the school; </inglise>
<eesti>2) esitab kooli k&otilde;rgemalseisvale asutusele taotluse kooli eelarveliseks finantseerimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) submit an application for the budgetary financing/ funding of the school to the superior agency of the school; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kuulab &auml;ra direktori aruande kooli eelarve t&auml;itmise kohta ning edastab selle koos omapoolse hinnanguga riigikooli puhul ministeeriumile, kelle valitsemisalasse kool kuulub, munitsipaalkooli puhul vastavale valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) hear the report of the head of the school on implementation of the school budget and shall forward it together with an assessment of the board, in the case of a state school, to the minister in whose area of government the school is located and, in the case of a municipal school, to the corresponding rural municipality or city government; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>3 (1)) kuulab &auml;ra direktori kava kooli eelarve kulude planeerimise kohta eelarveaastal ning edastab selle koos omapoolse hinnanguga riigikooli puhul ministeeriumile, kelle valitsemisalasse kool kuulub, munitsipaalkooli puhul vastavale valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele; </eesti>
<inglise>3 (1)) hear the plan of the head of the school on planning of the school budget of expenditure for a budgetary year and shall forward it together with an assessment of the board, in the case of a state school, to the minister in whose area of government the school is located and, in the case of a municipal school, to the corresponding rural municipality or city government; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>4) kuulab &auml;ra kooli direktori ja tema aset&auml;itjate aruanded ning v&otilde;tab vastu sellest tulenevaid otsuseid; </eesti>
<inglise>4) hear reports of the head of the school and his or her deputies and adopt decisions arising therefrom; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kinnitab otsusega riigi- ja kohaliku omavalitsuse asutused, avalik- ja era&otilde;iguslikud juriidilised isikud ning f&uuml;&uuml;silistest isikutest ettev&otilde;tjad, kus toimub &otilde;ppepraktika. </eesti>
<inglise>5) approve, by a resolution, state and local government agencies, legal persons in public law, legal persons in private law and sole proprietors where the practical training is conducted. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kooli n&otilde;ukogu teeb &uuml;ksikk&uuml;simustes otsuseid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A school board shall adopt resolutions in individual matters. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kooli n&otilde;ukogu tegutseb haridusministri m&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A school board shall operate pursuant to the procedure established by a regulation of the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli liikmeskond </eesti>
<inglise>Members of Schools </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Liikmeskond </eesti>
<inglise>Members </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kooli liikmeskonna moodustavad kooli pedagoogid ja teised t&ouml;&ouml;tajad (edaspidi personal) ning &otilde;pilased ja &uuml;li&otilde;pilased (edaspidi &otilde;pilased). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Teachers and other employees (hereinafter staff), and pupils and students (hereinafter students) are the members of a school. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on &uuml;li&otilde;pilaseks kutsek&otilde;rghariduse &otilde;ppekava j&auml;rgi &otilde;ppija. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Within the meaning of this Act, those studying according to a curriculum of higher vocational education are students. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;li&otilde;pilastele laienevad k&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud &otilde;igused ja kohustused niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd rakendusk&otilde;rgkooli seadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>The rights and obligations established by this Act apply to students acquiring higher vocational education in so far as the Institutions of Applied Higher Education Act does not provide otherwise. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Personal </eesti>
<inglise>Staff </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Personali t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesanded ja -kohustused m&auml;&auml;rab kooli direktor t&ouml;&ouml;suhteid reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The head of a school shall determine the duties of the members of the staff pursuant to legislation regulating employment relations. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Personaliga s&otilde;lmib, muudab ja l&otilde;petab t&ouml;&ouml;lepingud kooli direktor. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The head of a school shall enter into, amend or terminate employment contracts with the members of the staff. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Pedagoogid </eesti>
<inglise>Teachers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses k&auml;sitletakse pedagoogidena &otilde;ppealal t&ouml;&ouml;tavaid isikuid ning direktorit. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, persons engaged in the educational activities and heads of school are deemed to be teachers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kooli pedagoogi vaba ametikoht t&auml;idetakse avaliku konkursi korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A vacant position of a teacher in a school shall be filled by way of public competition. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Pedagoogide kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;uded kehtestab haridusminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The qualification requirements for teachers shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kooli pedagoogide vabade ametikohtade t&auml;itmiseks korraldatava konkursi tingimused ja korra kinnitab haridusminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The conditions and procedure for a competition organised to fill vacant positions of teachers in schools shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Pedagoogi vastavus ametikohale m&auml;&auml;ratakse atesteerimisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The suitability of a teacher for a position shall be determined by evaluation. </inglise>
<eesti>Atesteerimise tingimused ja korra kehtestab haridusminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The evaluation conditions and procedure established by a regulation of the Minister of Education. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Pedagoogi t&ouml;&ouml;tasustamise aluseks on ametikoht. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The remuneration of a teacher shall be based on his or her position. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;pilase &otilde;igused ja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights and obligations of students </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;pilasel on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Students have the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) valida oma huvidele ja v&otilde;imetele vastav kool; </eesti>
<inglise>1) choose a school which suits their interests and abilities; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tutvuda enne kooli &otilde;ppima asumist kooli &otilde;ppekava, p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse ning sisekorra- ja &otilde;ppekorralduse eeskirjadega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) examine the curriculum, statutes and rules for internal procedure and organisation of studies of the school before commencing their studies at school; </inglise>
<eesti>3) valida &otilde;ppeaineid valik- ja vabaainete piires; </eesti>
<inglise>3) choose subjects from among elective and optional subjects; </inglise>
<eesti>4) osaleda &otilde;pilasesinduse moodustamises ning selle tegevuses; </eesti>
<inglise>4) participate in the formation of a student representative board and in the activities thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>5) osaleda kooli n&otilde;ukogusse valitud &otilde;pilasesinduse esindajate kaudu kooli n&otilde;ukogu tegevuses; </eesti>
<inglise>5) participate in the activities of a school board through the representatives of the student representative board elected to the school board; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kasutada &otilde;ppev&auml;lises tegevuses tasuta oma kooli ruume, raamatukogu, &otilde;ppe-, spordi-, tehnilisi ja muid vahendeid kooli poolt kehtestatud korras; </eesti>
<inglise>6) use the rooms, library, teaching aids, sports and technical equipment and other resources of their school in extracurricular activities without charge pursuant to the procedure established by the school; </inglise>
<eesti>7) saada Vabariigi Valitsuse ja kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu kehtestatud korras ainelist abi v&otilde;i soodustusi; </eesti>
<inglise>7) receive material assistance or be granted concessions pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic and the local government council; </inglise>
<eesti>7 (1)) saada &otilde;pilaspilet; </eesti>
<inglise>7 (1)) receive student cards; </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>8) saada &otilde;ppelaenu seadusega kehtestatud tingimustel ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud korras; </eesti>
<inglise>8) receive a student loan under the conditions established by law and pursuant to the procedure established by legislation issued on the basis thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>9) kasutada muid seaduse ja kooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatud &otilde;igusi. </eesti>
<inglise>9) exercise other rights established by law and the statutes of the school. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kool tagab &otilde;pilase koolis viibimise ajal tema tervise kaitse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A school shall ensure the health protection of students during their stay at the school. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli asukohaj&auml;rgne valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus m&auml;&auml;rab &otilde;pilaste meditsiinilise teenindamise korra. </eesti>
<inglise>The rural municipality government or city government of the location of the school shall determine the procedure for the medical surveillance of students. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;pilane peab j&auml;rgima seaduse, kooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse, sisekorraeeskirja ja muude &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud kohustusi ning kandma vastutust nende rikkumise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Students shall observe the obligations established by law, the statutes and internal procedure rules of the school, and other legislation, and bear liability upon violation thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;pilaskond ja &otilde;pilasesindus </eesti>
<inglise>Student body and student representative board </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kooli &otilde;pilased moodustavad &uuml;he &otilde;pilaskonna. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Students of a school form one student body. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&auml;iskasvanute t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe kursuste kuulajad &otilde;pilaskonda ei kuulu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Participants in adult in-service training courses shall not be members of a student body. </inglise>
<eesti>Nende &otilde;igusliku seisundi m&auml;&auml;rab t&auml;iskasvanute koolituse seadus (RT I 1993, 74, 1054; 1998, 71, 2100; 1999, 10, 150; 60, 617). </eesti>
<inglise>The legal status of such persons is determined by the Adult Education Act (RT I 1993, 74, 1054; 1998, 71, 2100; 1999, 10, 150; 60, 617). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;pilaskonnal on &otilde;igus otsustada ja korraldada iseseisvalt, koosk&otilde;las seaduse ja seaduse alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidega, &otilde;pilaselu k&uuml;simusi, l&auml;htudes &otilde;pilaste huvidest, vajadustest, &otilde;igustest ja kohustustest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Student bodies have the right to decide and manage independently, in accordance with law and legislation issued on the basis thereof, issues of student life based on the interests, needs, rights and obligations of students. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Otilde;pilaskonnal on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Student bodies have the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) moodustada teiste &otilde;pilaskondadega liite ja organisatsioone &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras; </eesti>
<inglise>1) form associations and organisations with other student bodies on the bases and pursuant to the procedure provided by legislation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) astuda vastavate rahvusvaheliste organisatsioonide liikmeks v&otilde;i arendada nendega koost&ouml;&ouml;d; </eesti>
<inglise>2) become members of corresponding international organisations or develop co-operation with such organisations; </inglise>
<eesti>3) valida oma esindajaid kooli n&otilde;ukogusse; </eesti>
<inglise>3) elect their representatives to the school board; </inglise>
<eesti>4) otsustada ja korraldada k&otilde;iki muid &otilde;pilaselu k&uuml;simusi, mis seaduse ja seaduse alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt kuuluvad &otilde;pilaskonna p&auml;devusse ning mis ei ole samadel alustel antud kellegi teise otsustada ja korraldada. </eesti>
<inglise>4) decide and manage all other issues of student life which pursuant to law and legislation issued on the basis thereof are within the competence of a student body and which on the same grounds have not been transferred to any other person to decide or manage. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Otilde;pilaskonnal on p&otilde;hikiri, milles s&auml;testatakse &otilde;pilaskonna esindus- ja t&auml;itevorganite moodustamise kord, nende &otilde;igused, kohustused ja vastutus ning t&ouml;&ouml;kord. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Student bodies have statutes which provide the procedure for the formation of students' representative and executive bodies, and for the rights, obligations, liability, and rules of procedure thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) &Otilde;pilaskonna p&otilde;hikirja v&otilde;tab vastu &otilde;pilaskond kooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A student body shall adopt its statutes pursuant to the procedure provided for in the statutes of the school. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;pilasesindus esitab &otilde;pilaskonna p&otilde;hikirja kooli n&otilde;ukogule kinnitamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The student representative board shall submit the statutes of the student body to the school board for approval. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli n&otilde;ukogu kinnitab &otilde;pilaskonna p&otilde;hikirja, kui see vastab seadusele, seaduse alusel antud &otilde;igusaktidele ja rahvusvaheliselt tunnustatud demokraatlikele p&otilde;him&otilde;tetele. </eesti>
<inglise>The school board shall approve the statutes of the student body if the statutes comply with law, legislation issued on the basis thereof and internationally recognised democratic principles. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) &Otilde;pilaskonna vastutav ja korraldav esindusorgan on demokraatlikult valitud &otilde;pilasesindus, kes esindab &otilde;pilaskonda suhetes kooliga, Eesti ja rahvusvaheliste organisatsioonide, asutuste ja isikutega. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The responsible representative body which governs a student body is the student representative board which is elected democratically and which represents the student body in relations with the school and with Estonian and international organisations, agencies and persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) &Otilde;pilasesinduse valimise &otilde;igus on k&otilde;ikidel kooli &otilde;pilastel. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) All students of a school have the right to elect the student representative board. </inglise>
<eesti>Esimese &otilde;pilasesinduse valimised korraldab direktor kooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korras, l&auml;htudes demokraatlikest printsiipidest. </eesti>
<inglise>The head shall organise the elections of the first student representative board pursuant to the procedure provided for in the statutes of the school based on democratic principles. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli finantseerimine ja eelarve </eesti>
<inglise>Financing and Budgets of Schools </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli finantseerimine ja eelarve </eesti>
<inglise>Financing and budgets of schools </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kooli finantseeritakse riigieelarvest, valla- v&otilde;i linnaeelarvest, kooli p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud kooli p&otilde;hitegevusega seotud tasulistest teenustest, laekumistest sihtasutustelt ja muudest vahenditest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Schools shall be financed from the state budget, rural municipality budget or city budget, fee-charging services related to the main activities of schools provided for in the statutes of the schools, revenue from foundations, and other funds. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigikooli &otilde;ppekulud kaetakse riigieelarvest selle ministeeriumi eelarve vahenditest, kelle valitsemisalasse kool kuulub. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The study costs of a state school shall be covered from the state budget from the budget funds of the ministry in whose area of government the school is located. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riigikooli &otilde;ppekulud kaetakse riigieelarve vahenditest riigi poolt finantseeritavate koolituskohtade arvu ulatuses &otilde;ppekavaga m&auml;&auml;ratud nominaalse &otilde;ppeaja jooksul, l&auml;htudes koolituskoha maksumusest ning &otilde;ppekavade ja &otilde;ppevormide koefitsientidest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The study costs of a state school shall be covered from the state budget funds within the limits of the number of student places financed by the state during the standard period of study determined in the curriculum, on the basis of the cost of a student place and the factors for the curricula and forms of study. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riigikooli riigi poolt finantseeritavad koolituskohad kinnitab p&auml;rast vastava kutsen&otilde;ukogu arvamuse &auml;rakuulamist minister, kelle juhitava ministeeriumi valitsemisalasse kool kuulub. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The minister who directs the ministry in whose area of government a school is located shall approve the student places of the state school which are financed by the state after having considered the opinion of the corresponding professional council. </inglise>
<eesti>Munitsipaalkooli valla- v&otilde;i linnaeelarvest finantseeritavad koolituskohad kinnitab p&auml;rast vastava kutsen&otilde;ukogu arvamuse &auml;rakuulamist valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>A rural municipality or city government shall approve the student places of the municipal school which are financed from the rural municipality or city budget after having considered the opinion of the corresponding professional council. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Koolituskoha maksumuse igaks eelarveaastaks kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The cost of a student place for each budgetary year shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppevaldkondade ja &otilde;ppevormide koefitsiendid ning koefitsiendid erivajadustega &otilde;pilastele &otilde;ppe l&auml;biviimiseks kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The factors for the fields of study and forms of study and the factors for the provision of instruction for students with special needs shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Munitsipaalkoolis p&otilde;hihariduse baasil &otilde;ppivate &otilde;pilaste &otilde;petamisega seotud &otilde;ppekulud kaetakse riigieelarve vahenditest k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The study costs related to the teaching of students studying in a municipal school on the basis of basic education shall be covered from the state budget funds on the bases specified in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigieelarve vahenditest v&otilde;ib kokkuleppel vastava valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusega l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud alustel katta ka munitsipaalkoolis keskhariduse baasil &otilde;ppivate &otilde;pilaste &otilde;petamisega seotud &otilde;ppekulud. </eesti>
<inglise>The study costs related to the teaching of students studying in a municipal school on the basis of secondary education may be covered from the state budget funds upon agreement with the corresponding rural municipality or city government on the bases specified in subsection (3). </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Munitsipaalkoolis keskhariduse baasil &otilde;ppivate &otilde;pilaste &otilde;petamisega seotud &otilde;ppekulude katmiseks riigieelarve vahenditest s&otilde;lmitakse vastava valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse ja Haridusministeeriumi kui riigi esindaja vahel leping. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) In order to cover the study costs related to the teaching of students studying in a municipal school on the basis of secondary education from the state budget funds, a contract shall be entered into between the corresponding rural municipality or city government and the Ministry of Education as the representative of the state. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingu kohustuslikud tingimused on: </eesti>
<inglise>The mandatory terms and conditions for the contract shall be: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koolituskohtade arv vastavalt &otilde;ppekavale ja &otilde;ppevormile; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the number of student places pursuant to the curriculum and form of study; </inglise>
<eesti>2) koolituskoha maksumus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the cost of a student place; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riigieelarvest raha eraldamise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the procedure for allocation of funds from the state budget; </inglise>
<eesti>4) riigi finantseeritavatel koolituskohtadel &otilde;ppivate &otilde;pilaste arvestuseks vajalike andmete esitamise kord ja t&auml;htajad; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the procedure and terms for submission of information necessary for the calculation of students studying at student places financed by the state; </inglise>
<eesti>5) poolte &otilde;igused ja kohustused; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the rights and obligations of the parties; </inglise>
<eesti>6) poolte vastutuse alused; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the bases for the liability of the parties; </inglise>
<eesti>7) &otilde;ppevaldkondade ja &otilde;ppevormide koefitsiendid. </eesti>
<inglise>7) the factors for the fields of study and forms of study. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) P&otilde;hiharidust omandavate isikute kutsealase eelkoolituse korraldamisega seotud kulud kaetakse riigikooli puhul riigieelarvest selle ministri kinnitatud koolituskohtade arvu ulatuses, kelle valitsemisalasse kool kuulub, munitsipaalkooli puhul valla- v&otilde;i linnaeelarvest vastava valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse kinnitatud koolituskohtade arvu ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The costs related to the organisation of preliminary vocational training for persons acquiring basic education shall be covered, in the case of state schools, from the state budget within the limits of the number of student places approved by the minister in whose area of government the school is located and, in the case of municipal schools, from the corresponding rural municipality or city budget within the limits of the number of student places approved by the rural municipality or city government. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigieelarve vahenditest v&otilde;ib vastava valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse ja Haridusministeeriumi kui riigi esindaja vahelise lepingu alusel katta ka munitsipaalkoolis p&otilde;hiharidust omandavate isikute kutsealase eelkoolituse korraldamisega seotud kulud. </eesti>
<inglise>The study costs related to the organisation of preliminary vocational training for persons acquiring basic education in municipal schools may be covered from the state budget funds on the basis of a contract between the corresponding rural municipality or city government and the Ministry of Education as the representative of the state. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingule kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 14 (1) l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud lepingu kohustuslikke tingimusi. </eesti>
<inglise>The mandatory terms and conditions for contracts specified in subsection 14 (1) (3) of this Act apply to the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Koolil on oma eelarve. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) A school shall have its own budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>7. Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku j&auml;relevalve teostajad </eesti>
<inglise>Authorities exercising state supervision </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet kooli &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatustegevuse &uuml;le teostavad Haridusministeerium ja maavanem (edaspidi riiklik j&auml;relevalveorgan). </eesti>
<inglise>The Ministry of Education and a county governor (hereinafter state supervisory agency) shall exercise state supervision over the schooling and education in schools. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklikul j&auml;relevalveorganil on &otilde;igus kaasata riikliku j&auml;relevalve teostamisele eksperte. </eesti>
<inglise>The state supervisory agency has the right to involve experts in the exercise of state supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku j&auml;relevalve eesm&auml;rk ja riikliku j&auml;relevalveorgani &uuml;lesanded </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of state supervision and functions of state supervisory agency </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riikliku j&auml;relevalve eesm&auml;rk on tagada &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatustegevuse efektiivsus ning seaduslikkus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The objective of state supervision is to ensure the effectiveness and legality of schooling and education. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riikliku j&auml;relevalve p&otilde;hieesm&auml;rgist tulenevalt on riiklikul j&auml;relevalveorganil j&auml;rgmised &uuml;lesanded: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Based on the principal objective of state supervision, the functions of a state supervisory agency are the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) anal&uuml;&uuml;sida ja hinnata kooli &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatustegevuse ning juhtimise tulemuslikkust; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to analyse and evaluate the efficiency of schooling and education and management of schools; </inglise>
<eesti>2) hinnata &otilde;pitulemuste vastavust riiklikule &otilde;ppekavale; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to evaluate the conformity of study results to the national curriculum; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kontrollida &otilde;igusaktidest tulenevate n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to monitor the compliance with the requirements arising from legislation; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kontrollida riigieelarvest koolile eraldatud vahendite ning kooli kasutuses v&otilde;i valduses oleva riigivara kasutamise seaduslikkust ja otstarbekust; </eesti>
<inglise>4) to monitor the legality and purposefulness of the use of funds allocated for schools from the state budget and state assets in the use or control of schools; </inglise>
<eesti>5) n&otilde;ustada kooli &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatustegevuse ning haridus&ouml;konoomika k&uuml;simustes; </eesti>
<inglise>5) to advise schools on issues of schooling and education, and of the financial management of education; </inglise>
<eesti>6) anal&uuml;&uuml;sida kutsekeskhariduse taset ning kutsek&otilde;rghariduse &otilde;ppekava j&auml;rgi omandatava k&otilde;rghariduse taset. </eesti>
<inglise>6) to analyse the level of secondary vocational education and the level of higher education acquired according to a curriculum of higher vocational education. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34 (2). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku j&auml;relevalveorgani p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Competence of state supervisory agency </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks on riiklikul j&auml;relevalveorganil &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For performance of its functions, a state supervisory agency has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&uuml;lastada direktori teadmisel &otilde;ppetunde; </eesti>
<inglise>1) attend lessons with the knowledge of the head of the school; </inglise>
<eesti>2) osaleda kooli &otilde;ppen&otilde;ukogu ja kooli n&otilde;ukogu koosolekutel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) participate in the meetings of teachers' councils and school boards; </inglise>
<eesti>3) viia koolis l&auml;bi tasemet&ouml;id &otilde;ppetaseme kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) carry out standard-determining tests in schools in order to determine the level of education; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teha direktorile ettepanekuid kooli tegevuse parandamiseks ja ettekirjutusi &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatustegevuses esinevate puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) submit proposals to heads of schools in order to improve the activities of schools and issue precepts in order to eliminate the deficiencies in schooling and education; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teha direktorile ettekirjutusi tema poolt antud ja seadusega vastuolus olevate &otilde;igusaktide koosk&otilde;lla viimiseks kehtivate seadustega; </eesti>
<inglise>5) issue precepts to heads of schools to bring legislation issued by the heads of schools which is in conflict with a law into accordance with law; </inglise>
<eesti>6) teha direktorile ettekirjutusi riigieelarvest koolile eraldatud vahendite ning kooli kasutuses v&otilde;i valduses oleva riigivara seaduslikuks ja otstarbekaks kasutamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>6) issue precepts to heads of schools for the legal and purposeful use of funds allocated for schools from the state budget and state assets in the use or control of the schools; </inglise>
<eesti>7) teha ministeeriumile, kelle valitsemisalasse kool kuulub, v&otilde;i valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele ettepanekuid kooli &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatustegevuse tingimuste parandamiseks v&otilde;i direktori distsiplinaarkorras karistamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>7) submit proposals to the minister in whose area of government a school is located, or to a rural municipality and city government in order to improve the conditions of schooling and education or to punish the head of a school under disciplinary procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel on riiklik j&auml;relevalveorgan kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon performance of its functions, a state supervisory agency is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) olema hinnangutes erapooletu, tuginema oma otsustustes &otilde;igusaktidele ja usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsele teabele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) be impartial in assessments, and base its decisions on legislation and reliable information; </inglise>
<eesti>2) arvestama kooli &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatustegevusele &uuml;ldhinnangu andmisel kompleksse anal&uuml;&uuml;si tulemusi. </eesti>
<inglise>2) take into account the results of integrated analysis when providing a general evaluation of the schooling and education of a school. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34 (3). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34 (3). </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku j&auml;relevalve l&auml;biviimine </eesti>
<inglise>Exercise of state supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riikliku j&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus kontrollitakse kooli tegevust kompleksselt v&otilde;i &uuml;ksikk&uuml;simustes. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the course of state supervision, the activities of a school shall be monitored integrately or in individual matters. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riikliku j&auml;relevalve l&auml;biviimise aja, kontrollimise kava ja riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet l&auml;biviivad ametnikud kinnitab haridusminister v&otilde;i maavanem. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Education or a county governor shall approve the time of exercise of state supervision, a monitoring plan and the officials exercising state supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kontrollimise kestus ei tohi &uuml;letada kaht n&auml;dalat. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The duration of monitoring shall not exceed two weeks. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riikliku j&auml;relevalve l&auml;biviimisest teavitatakse kooli direktorit, munitsipaalkooli puhul ka valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsust, v&auml;hemalt 10 p&auml;eva enne kontrollimise algust, edastades neile kontrollimise kava. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The head of a school, and in the case of a municipal school, also the rural municipality or city government shall be notified of exercise of state supervision at least ten days before monitoring and a monitoring plan shall be communicated to them. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ksikk&uuml;simuste kontrollimisest ei pea eelnevalt informeerima kooli direktorit ega munitsipaalkooli puhul vastavat valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsust. </eesti>
<inglise>The head of a school, and in the case of a municipal school, the corresponding rural municipality or city government need not be informed in advance of the monitoring of individual matters. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34 (4). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34 (4). </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku j&auml;relevalve tulemused </eesti>
<inglise>Results of state supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riikliku j&auml;relevalve tulemused vormistatakse kontrollaktiga, kui kooli tegevust kontrolliti kompleksselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The results of state supervision shall be documented in a report if the activities of a school are monitored integrately. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ksikk&uuml;simuste kontrollimine vormistatakse &otilde;iendiga. </eesti>
<inglise>The monitoring of individual matters shall be documented in a certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>Kontrollakti v&otilde;i &otilde;iendi kinnitab haridusminister v&otilde;i maavanem. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Education or the county governor shall approve the reports and certificates. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kinnitatud kontrollakt v&otilde;i &otilde;iend edastatakse kooli direktorile ning munitsipaalkooli puhul vastavale valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele 30 p&auml;eva jooksul kontrollimise l&otilde;petamise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An approved report or certificate shall be forwarded to the head of the school, and in the case of a municipal school, to the corresponding rural municipality or city government within thirty days after the day when monitoring is terminated. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Maavanema kinnitatud kontrollakt v&otilde;i &otilde;iend edastatakse Haridusministeeriumile 10 p&auml;eva jooksul selle koolile edastamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A report or certificate approved by a county governor shall be forwarded to the Ministry of Education within ten days after the report or certificate is forwarded to a school. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riikliku j&auml;relevalveorgani tehtud ettekirjutused on t&auml;itmiseks kohustuslikud ettekirjutuses s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The precepts issued by a state supervisory agency are mandatory for execution during the term provided for in the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kontrollakti v&otilde;i &otilde;iendiga mitten&otilde;ustumisel on kooli direktoril &otilde;igus vaidlustada kontrollakt v&otilde;i &otilde;iend Haridusministeeriumis &uuml;he kuu jooksul kontrollakti v&otilde;i &otilde;iendi k&auml;ttesaamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon disagreement with a report or certificate, the head of a school has the right to contest the report or certificate in the Ministry of Education within one month after receipt of the report or certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli &uuml;mberkorraldamine, munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmine ja tegevuse l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Reorganisation, Transfer into Municipal or Private Ownership and Closure of Schools </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli &uuml;mberkorraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Reorganisation of school </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigikooli korraldab &uuml;mber Vabariigi Valitsus ministri ettepanekul, kelle juhitava ministeeriumi valitsemisalasse riigikool kuulub. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state school shall be reorganised by the Government of the Republic on the proposal of the minister who directs the ministry in whose area of government the state school is located. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Munitsipaalkooli &uuml;mberkorraldamise otsustab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse ettepanekul valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The reorganisation of a municipal school shall be decided by the rural municipality council or the city council on the proposal of the rural municipality government or city government. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kooli &uuml;mberkorraldamine v&otilde;ib toimuda j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Schools may be reorganised in the following cases: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koolitusn&otilde;udluse suurenemise v&otilde;i v&auml;henemise t&otilde;ttu antud piirkonnas; </eesti>
<inglise>1) due to an increase or decrease in the demand for training in the given region; </inglise>
<eesti>2) suurenenud v&otilde;i v&auml;henenud finantseerimisv&otilde;imaluste t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>2) due to increased or decreased funding possibilities; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;mberkorralduste t&otilde;ttu hariduss&uuml;steemis; </eesti>
<inglise>3) due to restructuring in the education system; </inglise>
<eesti>4) muudel seadusest tulenevatel juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) in other cases arising from law. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kooli &uuml;mberkorraldamine toimub p&auml;rast &otilde;ppeaasta l&otilde;ppu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Schools shall be reorganised after the end of an academic year. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Riigikooli &uuml;mberkorraldamine toimub Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) State schools shall be reorganised pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kooli &uuml;mberkorraldamise otsusest teatatakse Haridusministeeriumile, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui kool kuulub Haridusministeeriumi valitsemisalasse, ning &otilde;pilastele ja kooli personalile hiljemalt kuus kuud enne uue &otilde;ppeaasta algust. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A decision to reorganise a school shall be communicated to the Ministry of Education, except if the school is in the area of government of the Ministry of Education, and to the students and members of the school staff not later than six months before the beginning of an academic year. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of school into municipal or private ownership </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vabariigi Valitsusel on &otilde;igus haridusministri ettepanekul anda luba riigikooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmiseks k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On the proposal of the Minister of Education, the Government of the Republic has the right to grant permission for transfer of a state school into municipal or private ownership under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure provided for in this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigikooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmine toimub likvideerimismenetluseta ja riigikool antakse munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse koos k&otilde;igi tema &otilde;iguste, kohustuste, asjade ja muude &otilde;igush&uuml;vedega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A state school shall be transferred into municipal or private ownership without liquidation proceedings and the state school shall be transferred into municipal or private ownership together with all its rights, obligations, things and other legal rights. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle tulemusel moodustub munitsipaalkool v&otilde;i erakool ja riigikooli tegevus loetakse l&otilde;ppenuks. </eesti>
<inglise>This results in establishment of a municipal school or private school and the state school is deemed to be closed. </inglise>
<eesti>Samaaegselt riigikooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmisega v&auml;ljastatakse munitsipaal- ja erakoolile koolitusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>At the same time with transfer of the state school into municipal or private ownership, an education licence shall be issued to the municipal school or private school. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riigikooli v&otilde;ib anda munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A state school may be transferred into municipal or private ownership if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) see on otstarbekas kutsehariduss&uuml;steemi arengu seisukohalt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) this is necessary for the development of the vocational education system; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kooli juhtimine ning &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatustegevus munitsipaal- v&otilde;i erakoolina on tulemuslikum; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the management, schooling and education of the school as a municipal or private school are more effective; </inglise>
<eesti>3) koolil on munitsipaal- v&otilde;i erakoolina paremad v&otilde;imalused omandatava hariduse kvaliteedi tagamiseks, sealhulgas &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatustegevuse tingimuste parandamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) as a municipal or private school, the school has better possibilities to ensure the quality of the acquired education, including improvement of the conditions of schooling and education; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kool suudab munitsipaal- v&otilde;i erakoolina efektiivsemalt reageerida t&ouml;&ouml;turu n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>4) as a municipal or private school, the school is able to meet the requirements of the labour market more effectively. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riigikooli v&otilde;ib anda era&otilde;igusliku juriidilise isiku omandisse, mille &uuml;heks osaniku-, aktsion&auml;ri-, asutaja- v&otilde;i liikme&otilde;iguse teostajaks on riik v&otilde;i vald v&otilde;i linn. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A state school may be transferred into the ownership of a legal person in private law also if one of the exercisers of the rights of a partner, shareholder, founder or member is the state or a rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Riigikooli munitsipaalomandisse andmiseks esitab valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu, riigikooli eraomandisse andmiseks aga era&otilde;igusliku juriidilise isiku vastav organ haridusministrile taotluse, mis peab sisaldama andmeid k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud tingimuste t&auml;itmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In order to transfer a state school into municipal ownership, the rural municipality or city council, and in order to transfer a state school into private ownership, the corresponding body of the legal person in private law shall submit an application to the Minister of Education and the application shall include information concerning fulfilment of the requirements specified in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Samaaegselt riigikooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmise taotlusega taotletakse &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud tingimustel ja korras munitsipaalkoolile v&otilde;i erakoolile koolitusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>At the same time with the application for transfer of the state school into municipal or private ownership, an education licence shall be applied for for the municipal or private school under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure provided for in legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Haridusminister otsustab Vabariigi Valitsuselt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud loa taotlemise, kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud tingimused ja &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud koolitusloa saamise tingimused on t&auml;idetud. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Minister of Education shall decide on application for the permission specified in subsection (1) of this section if the requirements specified in subsection (3) of this section and the requirements for the obtaining of an education licence provided for in legislation are fulfilled. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Vabariigi Valitsus annab loa riigikooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmiseks, kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud tingimused on t&auml;idetud, ja volitab haridusministrit s&otilde;lmima riigikooli munitsipaal- ja eraomandisse andmise kohta lepingut. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The Government of the Republic shall grant permission for transfer of a state school into municipal or private ownership if the requirements specified in subsection (3) of this section are fulfilled, and shall authorise the Minister of Education to enter into a contract with regard to transfer of the state school into municipal or private ownership. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Riigikooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmine s&auml;testatakse vastavalt valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu v&otilde;i era&otilde;igusliku juriidilise isiku organi ja Vabariigi Valitsuse volitusel haridusministri vahel k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel s&otilde;lmitavas lepingus. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The transfer of a state school into municipal or private ownership shall be provided for in a contract entered into pursuant to this Act between the rural municipality or city council or the body of the legal person in private law, respectively, and the Minister of Education by authorisation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingu kohustuslikud tingimused on: </eesti>
<inglise>The mandatory terms and conditions for the contract shall be: </inglise>
<eesti>1) riigikooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmise kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the date of transfer of the state school into municipal or private ownership; </inglise>
<eesti>2) munitsipaalkooli v&otilde;i erakooli &uuml;lesanded; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the functions of the municipal school or private school; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &otilde;ppekavad, mille alusel riigikooli &otilde;pilased j&auml;tkavad &otilde;pinguid munitsipaalkoolis v&otilde;i erakoolis; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the curricula on the basis of which the students of the state school continue studies in the municipal school or private school; </inglise>
<eesti>4) riigikooli &otilde;pilaste &otilde;pingute j&auml;tkamise tingimused ja kord munitsipaalkoolis v&otilde;i erakoolis; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the conditions and procedure for the students of the state school for continuation of studies in the municipal school or private school; </inglise>
<eesti>5) riigikooli t&ouml;&ouml;tajate t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;tkamise tingimused ja kord munitsipaalkoolis v&otilde;i erakoolis t&ouml;&ouml;suhteid reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud alustel, tingimustel ja korras; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the conditions and procedure for the employees of the state school for continuation of employment in the municipal school or private school on the bases, under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure provided for in legislation regulating employment relations; </inglise>
<eesti>6) riigikooli kasutuses oleva riigivara vallale v&otilde;i linnale v&otilde;i era&otilde;iguslikule juriidilisele isikule &uuml;leandmise tingimused, kord ja t&auml;htaeg &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud alustel, tingimustel ja korras; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the conditions, procedure and term for transfer of the state assets in the use of the state school to the rural municipality or city or legal person in private law on the bases, under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure provided for in legislation; </inglise>
<eesti>7) riigikooli asjaajamise vallale v&otilde;i linnale v&otilde;i era&otilde;iguslikule juriidilisele isikule &uuml;leandmise tingimused, kord ja t&auml;htaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the conditions, procedure and term for transfer of the administration of the state school to the rural municipality or city or legal person in private law; </inglise>
<eesti>8) riigikooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmisega kaasnevate v&otilde;imalike organisatsiooniliste ja eelarveliste, sealhulgas koolituskoha maksumusest tulenevate k&uuml;simuste, ning muude varalisi kohustusi ja &otilde;igusi k&auml;sitlevate k&uuml;simuste lahendamine. </eesti>
<inglise>8) settlement of possible organisational and budgetary issues, including those arising from the cost of a student place, and other issues concerning proprietary obligations and rights resulting from the transfer of the state school into municipal or private ownership. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Riigikooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmisel tagavad Haridusministeerium ja vald v&otilde;i linn v&otilde;i era&otilde;iguslik juriidiline isik &otilde;pilastele v&otilde;imaluse j&auml;tkata &otilde;pinguid munitsipaalkoolis v&otilde;i erakoolis samal v&otilde;i l&auml;hedasel erialal. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Upon transfer of a state school into municipal or private ownership, the Ministry of Education and the rural municipality or city or the legal person in private law shall ensure students with an opportunity to continue studies in the municipal school or private school in the same or similar profession. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Riigikooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmine toimub p&auml;rast &otilde;ppeaasta l&otilde;ppu. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) A state school shall be transferred into municipal or private ownership after the end of an academic year. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigikooli munitsipaal- v&otilde;i eraomandisse andmise otsusest teatatakse &otilde;pilastele ja kooli personalile hiljemalt kaks kuud enne uue &otilde;ppeaasta algust. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision to transfer a state school into municipal or private ownership shall be communicated to the students and the staff of the school not later than two months before the beginning of an academic year. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2001 entered into force 22.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 375) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Kooli tegevuse l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Closure of schools </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigikooli tegevuse l&otilde;petab Vabariigi Valitsus ministri ettepanekul, kelle juhitava ministeeriumi valitsemisalasse riigikool kuulub. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A state school shall be closed by the Government of the Republic on the proposal of the minister who directs the ministry in whose area of government the state school is located. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Munitsipaalkooli tegevuse l&otilde;petamise otsustab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse ettepanekul linna- v&otilde;i vallavolikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The closure of a municipal school shall be decided by the city council or the rural municipality council on the proposal of the rural municipality government or city government. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kooli tegevus l&otilde;petatakse, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A school shall be closed if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kooli &otilde;ppe- ja kasvatustegevuse &uuml;le riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet teostava organi hinnangul ei vasta kooli &otilde;ppetase kutse-, eri- ja ametiala riikliku &otilde;ppekavaga kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) according to the body which exercises state supervision over the schooling and education in the school, the level of training in the school does not conform to the requirements established by the national curriculum of vocations, professions and occupations; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kooli ei ole v&otilde;imalik finantseerida; </eesti>
<inglise>2) financing of the school is impossible; </inglise>
<eesti>3) munitsipaalkooli k&otilde;ik koolitusload on t&uuml;histatud. </eesti>
<inglise>3) all education licences of the municipal school are revoked. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kooli tegevuse l&otilde;petamine toimub p&auml;rast &otilde;ppeaasta l&otilde;ppu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A school shall be closed after the end of an academic year. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kooli tegevuse l&otilde;petamisel tagab kooli k&otilde;rgemalseisev asutus &otilde;pilastele v&otilde;imaluse j&auml;tkata &otilde;pinguid teises koolis samal v&otilde;i l&auml;hedasel kutse-, eri- ja ametialal. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon the closure of a school, the superior agency of the school shall provide the students with an opportunity to continue studies in another school in the same or similar vocation, profession or occupation. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Riigikooli tegevuse l&otilde;petamine toimub Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A state school shall be closed pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kooli tegevuse l&otilde;petamise otsusest teatatakse Haridusministeeriumile, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui kool kuulub Haridusministeeriumi valitsemisalasse, ning &otilde;pilastele ja kooli personalile hiljemalt kuus kuud enne uue &otilde;ppeaasta algust. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The decision to close a school shall be communicated to the Ministry of Education, except if the school is in the area of government of the Ministry of Education, and to the students and the members of school staff not later than six months before the beginning of an academic year. </inglise>
